    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey so im studying for my materials class and im a bit stuck. why do we actually need to put steel rebar inside concrete for foundations? i get that concrete is strong, but whats the deal with needing the steel for tensile strength specifically? how do they work together?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Steel rebar is essential in concrete foundations because concrete, while great in compression, is very weak when it comes to tension. Think of it like a very strong, but brittle, material that cracks easily under pulling forces. The steel rebar, on the other hand, is incredibly strong in tension, which is why it's included to handle those pulling stresses that the concrete alone couldn't manage. This partnership, where concrete handles the squeezing and steel handles the stretching, creates a composite material that is much stronger overall.",
      "source": "target",
